Privacy Policy for PDF Editor All PDF Tools

Effective date: March 11, 2026

PDF Editor All PDF Tools (“we,” “our,” or “us”) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how the app collects, uses, and protects information when you use PDF Editor All PDF Tools.

1. Information We Collect

PDF Editor All PDF Tools is mainly designed to process files on your device. Depending on the features you use, the app may access:

- PDF files and documents selected by you
- Images selected by you for image to PDF features
- Camera access, if you use scan document features
- Device and app information required for app performance, analytics, and advertising

We do not collect your personal documents for our own use. Your files are processed locally on your device unless you choose to share, export, or open external links.

2. How We Use Information

We use information only to provide app features such as:

- Reading PDF files
- Merging PDF files
- Splitting PDF files
- Converting image to PDF
- Converting PDF to image
- Compressing PDF files
- Rotating PDF pages
- Locking and unlocking PDF files
- Adding watermark to PDF
- Reordering, removing, and extracting PDF pages
- Adding page numbers
- Saving recent files and app settings
- Displaying ads, if ads are enabled in the app

3. File Access and Storage

The app may request file or storage permissions so you can open, edit, save, and manage PDF files on your device.

All file operations are performed only to provide the features you choose to use.

4. Camera Permission

If you use document scan features, the app may request camera permission. Camera access is used only for scanning and creating PDF files from captured images.

5. Advertising

PDF Editor All PDF Tools may use Google AdMob to display ads. AdMob may collect and process certain information, such as:

- Device identifiers
- Advertising ID
- IP address
- App interaction data
- Diagnostics and performance data

This information is handled according to Google’s privacy policies.

Google Privacy Policy:
https://policies.google.com/privacy

6. Data Sharing

We do not sell your personal data.

We may share limited information only with trusted third-party service providers that support app functionality, such as advertising services, and only as necessary for those services to operate.

7. Data Security

We take reasonable steps to protect your data. Most PDF processing happens locally on your device. However, no method of storage or transmission is completely secure.

8. Children’s Privacy

PDF Editor All PDF Tools is not intended to knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided personal information through the app, please contact us so we can address the issue.

9. Your Choices

You can:

- Deny permissions such as camera or file access
- Stop using features that require those permissions
- Clear app data at any time
- Uninstall the app at any time

10. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date.

